title.narrative: CHILD PROTECTION IN EMERGENCY

description.narrative: By 2025, children and women in humanitarian situations and crises are safer and access better quality protection services., which contributes to Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, children are safer and better protected from violence, abuse, exploitation and harm.

description.narrative: UNICEF programmes reached 212,029 people (65 per cent children) with child protection services ranging from mental health and psychosocial support, specialized services for survivors of sexual violence, family tracing for unaccompanied and separated children, rights-based awareness and comprehensive community reintegration services for children formerly associated with armed groups and forces.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:06/01/2022
